This paper focuses on improving the response time of Deep Learning models on GPUs through benchmarking and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), followed by cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision), as these fields heavily rely on DL models and GPU acceleration. The paper also discusses optimizations related to framework inefficiency and layer fusion, which fall under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AR (Hardware Architecture), respectively.
